```julia
function add_yearmonth(df::DataFrame)
    return hcat(df, :ym => map(x -> string(x.year) * string(lpad(x.month, 2, '0')), df.dt))
end
```

This function uses the `:ym` destructuring assignment to create a new column named `ym` from the existing `dt` column. It applies the anonymous function to each row of the `dt` column, extracting the year and month components as integers, padding the month with zeros if necessary, and concatenating them into a string in the format "yyyymm". Finally, it uses `hcat` to add the new column to the DataFrame.
